Understanding the CIA Triad
Confidentiality
Definition

Confidentiality is the practice of ensuring that sensitive information is accessible only to authorized individuals. It protects data from unauthorized disclosure.

Importance
Safeguards personal and organizational information.
Prevents identity theft and data leakage.
Builds trust between organizations and users.
Example

A hospital stores patient records in a secure database where only doctors and authorized staff can access the information.

Integrity
Definition

Integrity means keeping information accurate, complete, and protected from unauthorized modifications.

Importance
Ensures reliable information.
Prevents accidental or malicious data changes.
Supports informed decision-making.
Example

An online examination system allows only authorized administrators to edit students' grades.

Availability
Definition

Availability ensures that systems, applications, and information remain accessible whenever authorized users require them.

Importance
Supports continuous operations.
Reduces service interruptions.
Improves user satisfaction.
Example

A university website uses backup servers to remain accessible during periods of high traffic or server failures.